ORWORB UNSIG ORDERS FOLLOWUP.descr: After viewing unsigned orders for a patient via an alert, evaluateswhether the alert should be deleted for the current user. The following two exception conditions exist when determining how alertdeletion will occur.  In all other cases, alert deletion will occur whenthe patient has no unsigned orders. 1)      If the recipient of this alert does NOT have the ORES key, thealert will be deleted for that recipient after he reviews the unsignedorders.  2)      If the recipient has the ORES key and is NOT linked to the patientas attending, inpatient primary provider or via OE/RR teams, his alertwill be deleted when his unsigned orders are signed.  (If unsigned orderswritten by other providers for the patient remain, alerts for these other providers will not be deleted.)  For example, a consulting surgeon (withORES) places three unsigned orders for a patient.  He then receives an "Order requires electronic signature" alert for the patient.  He uses the View Alerts follow-up action and is presented with ten unsigned orders forthe patient.  Only three of the ten orders are his.  The surgeon signs histhree unsigned orders.  If the surgeon is not linked to the patient asattending, inpatient primary providers or via OE/RR teams, the alert will be deleted (for him only.)   In most cases alert deletion will occur when the patient has no unsignedorders.  For example, if a recipient has the ORES key and is linked to thepatient as attending, inpatient primary provider or via OE/RR teams, allunsigned orders for the patient must be signed before his alert isdeleted.

TIU FIELD CAN EDIT.descr: TRUE if the current user is allowed to edit template fields.

TIU FIELD CHECK.descr: Very similar to IMPORT^TIUSRVF, except does not save template fields.Resolves self referencing loops, and takes into account fields withthe same name already saved. rename XML fields

TIU FIELD DOLMTEXT.descr: Reads through an array of text and converts all entries of templatefields to their assocaited List Manager text values. ie/ fills in text in template places - would be user independent

TIU FIELD EXPORT.descr: Exports Template Fields in XML format 8927.1 - [K/META] ... kind of utility

TIU FIELD IMPORT.descr: Imports Template Fields from XML format [K/META]

TIU FIELD LIST IMPORT.descr: Takes TMP filled in with LIST ADD

TIU FIELD NAME IS UNIQUE.descr: [IS-A] [K/META] Returns TRUE if the template field name is unique 8927.1

TIU GET DS TITLES.descr: Like TIU DIV AND CLASS INFO, except CLASS 244 is hard coded

TIU GET DS URGENCIES.descr: unusual as comes from doc dd

TIU GET LINKED PRF NOTES.descr: Represents a complex set of filters to get meta on notes wanted. Tie into PRF - one of two in TIU.

TIU GET PN TITLES.descr: Will get Titles preferred by a user if they are defined. Same as TIU GET DS TITLES but hard codes class 8925.1 to IEN '3'

TIU GET REQUEST.descr: returns the variable pointer to the REQUESTINGPACKAGE REFERENCE (File #8925, Field #1405). This would be the record inthe Requesting Package (e.g., Consult/Request Tracking or Surgery) forwhich the resulting document has been entered in TIU.

TIU ID ATTACH ENTRY.descr: This RPC will attach a a document as an Interdisciplinary (ID) entry to anID Parent document. [DUZ] sends alert too

TIU ID CAN ATTACH.descr: This BOOLEAN RPC evaluates the question of whether a particular documentmay be attached as an entry to an Interdisciplinary Note (i.e., can thisdocument be an ID Child?). Based on doc types

TIU ID CAN RECEIVE.descr: This BOOLEAN RPC evaluates the question of whether a particular documentmay receive an entry as an Interdisciplinary Parent Note (i.e., can thisdocument be an ID Parent?). [DFN] [IS-A]

TIU ID DETACH ENTRY.descr: This call will remove an ID Entry from an Interdisciplinary Note.

TIU IDENTIFY CLINPROC CLASS.descr: This RPC gets the CLINICAL PROCEDURES TIU Document Definitionfile (#8925.1) IEN.

TIU IDENTIFY CONSULTS CLASS.descr: This RPC returns the record number of the class CONSULTS in the TIUDOCUMENT DEFINITION file (#8925.1). [QUERY] [K/META]

TIU IDENTIFY SURGERY CLASS.descr: This RPC returns the record number of the class identified by the CLNAMEparameter in the TIU DOCUMENT DEFINITION file (#8925.1).

TIU IS THIS A CLINPROC?.descr: This RPC evaluates whether or not a Title is under theCLINICAL PROCEDURES Class.

TIU IS THIS A CONSULT?.descr: BOOLEAN RPC which evaluates whether the title indicated is that of aconsult.

TIU IS THIS A SURGERY?.descr: BOOLEAN RPC which evaluates whether the title indicated is that of aSURGICAL REPORT or PROCEDURE REPORT (NON-O.R.).

TIU IS USER A PROVIDER?.descr: This Boolean RPC returns TRUE if the user was a known provider on the date specified - Checks USR CLASS PROVIDER AND 200 Person Class.

TIU IS USER A USR PROVIDER.descr: This Boolean RPC returns TRUE if the user was a member of USR CLASS PROVIDER on the date specified.

TIU ISPRF.descr: This RPC is to check to see if the passed in TIU DOCUMENT TITLE IEN is a Patient Record Flag TITLE. IEN lookup that is more complicated than most taking. PRF docs PATIENT RECORD FLAG CAT I and PATIENT RECORD FLAG CAT II

TIU LINK TO FLAG.descr: This RPC is used to link a Progress Note to a Patient Record Flag

TIU LONG LIST CONSULT TITLES.descr: Long list for CLINICAL PROCEDURE doc types only

TIU NOTES.descr: This API gets lists of progress notes for a patient, with optional parameters for STATUS, EARLY DATE/TIME, and LATE DATE/TIME. [DFN] [QUERY]

TIU NOTES 16 BIT.descr: This API gets lists of progress notes for a patient, with optional parameters for STATUS, EARLY DATE/TIME, and LATE DATE/TIME. [DFN] [QUERY]

TIU NOTES BY VISIT.descr: This API gets lists of Progress Notes by visit from TIU. [DFN] [QUERY]

TIU ONE VISIT NOTE?.descr: Boolean RPC to evaulate if note has a corresponding visit. [DFN] [IS-A]

TIU REM DLG OK AS TEMPLATE.descr: TRUE is the passed in reminder dialog is allowed to be used ina TIU Template.

TIU REMINDER DIALOGS.descr: a list of reminder dialogs allowed for use as Templates.

TIU REQUIRES COSIGNATURE.descr: This Boolean RPC simply evaluates whether the current user requirescosignature for TIU DOCUMENTS, and returns a 1 if true, or a 0 if false.

TIU SIGN RECORD.descr: This API Supports the application of the user's electronic signature to aTIU document while evaluating authorization, and validating the user selectronic signature.

TIU SUMMARIES.descr: This API gets lists of Discharge Summaries for a patient, with optional parameters for STATUS, EARLY DATE/TIME, and LATE DATE/TIME.

TIU SUMMARIES BY VISIT.descr: This API returns lists of Discharge Summaries by visit.

TIU TEMPLATE ALL TITLES.descr: [K/META] Returns a long list of all active titles.

TIU TEMPLATE CHECK BOILERPLATE.descr: This RPC will evaluate boilerplate passed in the input array, checking tosee whether any of the embedded objects are inactive, faulty, orambiguous.

TIU TEMPLATE PERSONAL OBJECTS.descr: a list or Patient Data Objects allowed in Personal Templates [DUZ]

TIU USER INACTIVE?.descr: [IS-A] [DUZ] evaluates user's DIUSER status and termination status when selected.Returns 0 if active 1 if inactive

TIU WHICH SIGNATURE ACTION.descr: This RPC infers whether the user is trying to sign or cosign the docuementin question, and indicates which ASU ACTION the GUI should pass to the TIUAUTHORIZATION RPC.

VAFCTFU CONVERT ICN TO DFN.descr: Given a patient Integration Control Number (ICN), this will returnthe patient Internal Entry Number (IEN) from the PATIENT file (#2). [QUERY] [DFN]

XUS CCOW VAULT PARAM.descr: from CPRS GUI Manual - Clinical Context Management (sometimes referred to as CCOW) is a way for graphical user interface (GUI) applications to synchronize their clinical context based on the Health Level 7 CCOW standard. In simple terms, this means that if CCOW compliant applications are sharing context and one of the applications changes to a different patient, the other applications will change to that patient as well. The VA purchased Sentillions Vergence context management software to work with VistA. Shared context for GUIs?

XUS DIVISION GET.comment: Optional DUZ - otherwise falls back on DUZ(2)

XWB DEFERRED CLEARALL.descr: CLEAR all the data known to this job in the ^XTMP global - Makes use of the list in ^TMP(“XWBHDL”,$J,handle).

XWB DIRECT RPC.descr: request that a RPC be run on aremote system. The data is passed by HL7 to the remote system as is thereturn value - unlike XWB REMOTE RPC, this is a blocking call

XWB GET VARIABLE VALUE.descr: Out of scope as directly sets or accesses globals

XWB REMOTE CLEAR.descr: CLEAR the data under a HANDLE in the ^XTMP global.

XWB REMOTE GETDATA.descr: return an ARRAY with what ever data has been sent back from the remote site.

XWB REMOTE RPC.descr: request that an application RPCbe run on a remote system. The data is passed by HL7 to the remote systemas is the return value.

XWB REMOTE STATUS CHECK.descr: return the status of a remote RPC
